main event: On 6 September 1966, at approximately 7:15 AM, Mr. James C. Gillette, a farmer and resident of Gillette, Wyoming, reported observing an unidentified flying object (UFO) near his home.
interesting points: The UFO was first sighted hovering over a nearby hill and was observed to make a rapid ascent into the sky before disappearing from view.
The object was described as being oval in shape, approximately 30-40 feet in diameter, and emitting a bright, white light.
The object was silent and exhibited no visible means of propulsion.
The incident is classified as an 'Unidentified' under Project Blue Book guidelines.
No further investigation is warranted at this time.
